{
  "version": 3,
  "html": "<article class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto\">\n\n  \n  <section class=\"gradient-slate-dark text-white p-5 md:p-10 rounded-2xl mb-8\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-4 text-white\">The Real Question Nobody's Asking</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl text-slate-200 leading-relaxed mb-4\">\n      Your family's been dealing with apagones for years now. You've probably already sent flashlights, rechargeable fans, maybe even a small generator. But here's the thing—you're thinking about solar, and suddenly there are <em>dozens</em> of options ranging from tiny foldable panels to full-blown systems that could power a small house.\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-300\">\n      The question isn't really \"solar panels OR power stations\"—it's which combination makes sense for your family's specific situation in Cuba. Because sending the wrong setup? That's money sitting on a roof doing nothing.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-10\">\n    <p>\n      Let me break down what I've learned from digging through hundreds of reviews and specs on these systems. Solar panels alone don't store power—they generate it. So unless your family has batteries already (unlikely), sending just panels means they can only use electricity while the sun's shining. Power stations, on the other hand, are basically big batteries with built-in inverters. Some come with panels, some don't.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      For Cuba specifically, you're dealing with a few realities: <strong>8-12 hour blackouts</strong> are common in many provinces. The electrical grid fluctuates wildly. Humidity and salt air eat through cheap electronics. And whatever you send needs to survive customs and potentially rough handling. Oh, and it needs to actually fit in a shipping container without costing you a fortune in freight.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n      The sweet spot? Usually a complete kit with panels, charge controller, and either batteries included or compatibility with locally-available batteries. Let's look at what's actually worth sending.\n    </p>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <div class=\"bg-sunglow/10 border-2 border-sunglow p-5 md:p-8 rounded-xl mb-10\">\n    <p class=\"text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3\">\n      <span class=\"text-flame\">Quick answer:</span> For most Cuban households dealing with regular blackouts, the <strong>Renogy Premium 400W Kit</strong> hits the sweet spot—complete system, excellent reviews, and the MPPT controller actually maximizes what you get from those panels. If budget allows for a whole-house solution, the ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH system is overkill in the best way.\n    </p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FG2VF2V2?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mt-4 inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n      See the Renogy 400W Kit →\n    </a>\n  </div>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6\">The One I'd Send to My Own Family</h2>\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl mb-8 ring-2 ring-lime ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-lime text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Editor's Pick</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/716Cn4QfDsL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Renogy Premium 400 Watt Solar Kit - complete system with MPPT controller\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0FG2VF2V2\" class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3\">Renogy Premium 400W 12V Solar Kit</h3>\n          <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-4\">\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">5★</span>\n            <span class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">505 reviews</span>\n            <span class=\"bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4\">\n            This is the <strong>new 2025 version</strong> and reviewers are raving. Four 100W panels, a 40A MPPT charge controller (not the cheaper PWM type), Bluetooth monitoring, Z-brackets for mounting, and all the cables. The MPPT controller alone can squeeze 15-30% more power from the panels compared to PWM—that matters when you're trying to charge batteries during Cuba's shorter winter days.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4 text-sm\">\n            <strong>Cuba reality check:</strong> You'll need to source 12V batteries locally or send them separately (heavy!). The Bluetooth module lets your family monitor the system from their phone—useful for troubleshooting when you're thousands of miles away.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"font-bold text-flame mb-4\">VERDICT: The most complete, highest-rated kit here. Worth the investment.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FG2VF2V2?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors\">\n            Check Price on Amazon →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">If You Want to Solve the Problem Forever</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">This is the \"go big or go home\" option. Not cheap. Not small. But it could genuinely make your family energy-independent.</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-xl ring-2 ring-sunglow ring-offset-2 ring-offset-white dark:ring-offset-slate-900\">\n      <span class=\"bg-sunglow text-raisin px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-4 inline-block\">Whole-House Solution</span>\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6\">\n        <div class=\"w-full md:w-64 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81audnUHPBL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH Complete Solar System with inverter and 12 panels\" class=\"rounded-xl w-full h-64 object-contain bg-slate-50\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0BQV4YG1T\" class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-3\">ECO-WORTHY 9.36KWH 2340W 48V Complete System</h3>\n          <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-4\">\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.4★</span>\n            <span class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm\">445 reviews</span>\n            <span class=\"bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4\">\n            <span class=\"text-4xl font-extrabold text-flame\">9.36 KWH</span> of storage capacity. That's enough to run a refrigerator, fans, lights, phone charging, and a TV through an entire night of blackout—and then some. Includes 12 panels (195W each), a 5000W all-in-one inverter/charger, and mounting hardware. Plug and play design means less wiring headaches.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4 text-sm\">\n            <strong>The catch:</strong> Shipping this monster will cost serious money, and you'll need roof space for 12 panels. But reviewers consistently mention it \"just works\" out of the box. For a family in the provinces dealing with daily 8+ hour outages, this changes everything.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"font-bold text-sunglow mb-4\">VERDICT: The nuclear option. Expensive but genuinely life-changing.</p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BQV4YG1T?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-full bg-raisin text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-raisin/90 transition-colors\">\n            See Full System Details →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"my-10\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4\">How Much Solar Does Your Family Actually Need?</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">Punch in the typical blackout hours and what they need to run. This'll tell you if you're over or under-buying.</p>\n    <solar-sizing>\n  </solar-sizing></section>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Solid Mid-Range Kits</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">Not everyone needs 9KWH of storage. These 400W kits cover the essentials without breaking the bank.</p>\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\">\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-44 md:w-48 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81NGDGKhAJL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 400W Solar Kit with MPPT controller\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B0BPY72B9R\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">ECO-WORTHY 400W Premium Kit</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.3★</span>\n              <span class=\"bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs\">$$$$$</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mb-3\">\n              Four 100W panels, 40A MPPT controller, Bluetooth module, Z-brackets. Very similar to the Renogy but slightly lower-rated. ECO-WORTHY has good Cuba track record based on what I've seen in forums.\n            </p>\n            <p class=\"font-semibold text-flame text-sm mb-3\">Good alternative if Renogy's out of stock.</p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BPY72B9R?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-royal font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">\n              Check Availability →\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      \n      <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-44 md:w-48 shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71Ps3BsTkML._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"ECO-WORTHY 200W Solar Panel Kit\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-48 object-contain bg-slate-50\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B09RZZHHHM\" class=\"text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">ECO-WORTHY 200W Starter Kit</h3>\n            <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n              <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n              <span class=\"bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs\">$$$$$</span>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 text-sm mb-3\">\n              Entry-level but well-reviewed. 30A PWM controller (less efficient than MPPT but simpler). Good for charging phones, running a fan or two, keeping lights on. Won't power a fridge.\n            </p>\n            <p class=\"font-semibold text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-3\">Best for: Apartments or as a backup system.</p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09RZZHHHM?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-royal font-semibold text-sm hover:underline\">\n              See Details →\n            </a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  \n  <blockquote class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl italic text-flame border-l-4 border-flame pl-6 my-10\">\n    \"200 watts keeps the phones charged. 400 watts runs the essentials. 800+ watts means your family stops worrying about blackouts entirely.\"\n  </blockquote>\n\n  \n  <section class=\"mb-12\">\n    <h2 class=\"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">When You Need Serious Wattage</h2>\n    <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6\">These 800W+ options are for families with roof space and real power needs. Just panels—you'll need to add controllers and batteries.</p>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-5 md:p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-6\">\n      <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-5\">\n        <div class=\"w-full sm:w-48 md:w-56 shrink-0\">\n          <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81sCnup-X5L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"Callsun 800W Solar Panel Kit - 8 panels\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-56 object-contain bg-slate-50\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n          <span class=\"bg-royal text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase mb-3 inline-block\">Best Panel Value</span>\n          <h3 data-asin=\"B0FZKR417P\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2\">Callsun 800W Kit (8x 100W Panels)</h3>\n          <div class=\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-3\">\n            <span class=\"bg-lime text-white px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold\">4.6★</span>\n            <span class=\"text-slate-500 text-sm\">465 reviews</span>\n            <span class=\"bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-2 py-1 rounded-full text-sm\">$$$$$</span>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-4\">\n            Eight 100W monocrystalline panels with high-efficiency design. Reviewers love the build quality and consistent output. Works with 12V, 24V, 48V, or 60V systems—flexible for whatever battery setup they have or can get locally.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm mb-4\">\n            <strong>Note:</strong> Panels only—no controller or batteries included. Your family will need to source a charge controller (40A+ recommended) and battery bank.\n          </p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FZKR417P?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-flame text-white font-semibold no-underline hover:bg-flame/90 transition-colors text-sm\">\n            Check Price →\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n    <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4\">\n      <div class=\"bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800/50 p-4 rounded-xl\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row md:flex-col gap-4\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-32 md:w-full shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71pz5YPEjGL._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"STAR 870W Solar Panels\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-32 md:h-36 object-contain bg-white\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B0DFBSBWDG\" class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white text-sm mb-1\">STAR 870W (2x 435W)</h3>\n            <span class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">4.2★ • $$$$$</span>\n            <p class=\"text-xs text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2\">Two massive 435W panels. Fewer panels = less mounting hassle. 48V/24V compatible.</p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DFBSBWDG?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-royal text-xs font-semibold hover:underline mt-2 inline-block\">View →</a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800/50 p-4 rounded-xl\">\n        <div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row md:flex-col gap-4\">\n          <div class=\"w-full sm:w-32 md:w-full shrink-0\">\n            <img src=\"https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/713HUQV3X8L._AC_UY218_.jpg\" alt=\"18BB 800W N-Type Solar Panels\" class=\"rounded-lg w-full h-32 md:h-36 object-contain bg-white\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"flex-1 min-w-0\">\n            <h3 data-asin=\"B0FFGTMG46\" class=\"font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white text-sm mb-1\">18BB 800W N-Type</h3>\n            <span class=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">4.3★ • $$$</span>\n            <p class=\"text-xs text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mt-2\">Mid-range price point! N-type cells are newer tech with better heat tolerance—good for Cuban rooftops.</p>\n            <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FFGTMG46?tag=veguitas-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-royal text-xs font-semibold hover:underline mt-2 inline-block\">View →</a>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div cla